      <div class="col-lg-9">
        <p>
          My name is Florian and I am 22 years old. After finishing school, I left my
          hometown Bayreuth for studying Politics and Economics at the University of Potsdam.
          However, after four semesters of introduction into both the political and economic
          sciences, I found out that the latter had become my main passion.
          Consequently, I moved to Mannheim to restart my undergraduate education at
          the University of Mannheim (BSc Economics).
        </p>
        <p>
          So far, I have not regretted this decision, but I am nevertheless aware
          of the shortcoming of current mainstream economics. Therefore, I am also
          active in the local Pluralist Economics group and devote a lot of my spare
          time to learn about alternative economic perspectives. I built this website
          to bring together many of the things I've learned (and that I am still
          learning) and which I consider to be useful for understand the economic sphere.
        </p>
      </div>
